<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="58" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1401]" pageId="16" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,222,248]" pageId="16" pageNumber="58">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. In habitus the species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Bassi &amp; Sáfián &amp; Léger &amp; Müller &amp; Kravchenko &amp; Poltavsky, 2021" authorityName="Bassi" authorityYear="2021" box="[721,865,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Ancylogastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ghanensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[721,865,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="58">A. ghanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[873,937,223,249]" pageId="16" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[873,937,223,249]" pageId="16" pageNumber="58" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[953,1020,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[234,1353,189,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-25@5.[226,1361,181,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Adults of Ancylogastra Bassi &amp; Poltavsky, gen. n. species. A. amphiaula (Meyrick), female, Malawi, Nyika National Park. 2. A. magnifica Bassi, sp. n., male holotype. 3. A. boireaui Bassi &amp; Sáfián, sp. n., male holotype. 4. A. gangraensis Bassi, Sáfián, Müller &amp; †Kravchenko, sp. n., male paratype. 5. A. endroedyi Bassi, sp. n., female holotype. 6. A. coronata Bassi, sp. n., female holotype. 7. A. burundiana Bassi, sp. n., male paratype. 8. A. ghanensis Bassi, sp. n., male holotype. Scale bars = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566021/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="58">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) described below, but with forewing termen wider with white ground colour and abdomen paler. In the male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1066,1147,259,286]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–24" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1808,1832]" captionTargetBox="[249,1324,200,1767]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[238,1350,181,1785]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 16–24. Male genitalia and abdominal sclerotisations of Ancylogastra Bassi &amp; Poltavsky, gen. n. species. 16. A. burundiana Bassi, sp. n., holotype; 17. The same, tergite of eighth abdominal segment; 18. A. ghanensis Bassi, sp. n., paratype GS 6220 GB; 19. The same, paratype GS 6246 GB, sternite of eighth abdominal segment; 20. The same, tergite of eighth abdominal segment; 21. A. gangraensis Bassi, Sáfián, Müller &amp; †Kravchenko, sp. n., paratype GS 6690 GB, Guinea; 22. The same, tergite of eighth abdominal segment; 23. The same, sternite of eighth abdominal segment; 24. The same, apex of phallus magnified. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566027" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566027/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="58">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) the phallus is cylindrical with an apical tooth. In the female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[656,740,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–33" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[220,1365,208,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-19@14.[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 29–33. Female genitalia of Ancylogastra Bassi &amp; Poltavsky, gen. n. species. 29. A. burundiana Bassi, sp. n., paratype GS 2829 GB; 30. The same, magnified to show the lateral extension of ductus bursae; 31. A. ghanensis Bassi, sp. n., paratype GS 6195 GB; 32. A. coronata Bassi, sp. n., holotype, magnified to show the lateral extension of ductus bursae; 33. The same, holotype. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566031/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="58">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
), the sterigma is larger and less pointed and the ductus bursae is larger and less sclerotised. This and the next two new species described below are very close to each other in having the female genitalia with the lateral extension of the ductus bursae membranous, very short, and delicate (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 29–33" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[220,1365,208,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-19@14.[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 29–33. Female genitalia of Ancylogastra Bassi &amp; Poltavsky, gen. n. species. 29. A. burundiana Bassi, sp. n., paratype GS 2829 GB; 30. The same, magnified to show the lateral extension of ductus bursae; 31. A. ghanensis Bassi, sp. n., paratype GS 6195 GB; 32. A. coronata Bassi, sp. n., holotype, magnified to show the lateral extension of ductus bursae; 33. The same, holotype. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566031/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="58">Figs 30–32</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
